export const SKILL_DOCS_URI = 'elementor://generatepage/skill-docs';
export const REFERENCE_DOCS_URI = 'elementor://generatepage/reference-docs';
export const EXAMPLES_DOCS_URI = 'elementor://generatepage/examples-docs';
export const DESIGN_GUIDELINES_DOCS_URI = 'elementor://generatepage/design-guidelines-docs';

export const skillDocs = "---\nname: generate-elementor-page\ndescription: Generate a ready-to-import Elementor V4 template JSON for a page, section, or any portion of a page from a user goal. Use when the request says build / generate / create / scaffold / compose / assemble / design a page, landing page, hero, pricing block, features section, CTA, footer, or any composition using Atomic widgets / V4 elements (`e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, `e-tabs`, etc.). Workflow: synthesize a global-class catalog, draft structure in **HTML/CSS (inline)**, get approval when required, then emit JSON + companion so globals carry layout and style. Output is a single JSON file the user can drop into Elementor → Templates → Import.\n---\n\n# Generate Elementor V4 Page\n\n## Persistence target\n\nWhen using the `generate-page` MCP tool, persist the generated V4 content to the **current editor page by default**. Do not create a new WordPress page unless the user explicitly asks for a new page. In tool input terms:\n\n- Default path: omit `createNewPage` or set it to `false`; the tool updates the current editor page.\n- New-page path: set `createNewPage: true` only when the user explicitly asks to create a new page; then provide `pageTitle`.\n- `dbContent` is always the bare V4 content array JSON string saved to `_elementor_data`.\n- `classesContent` is optional companion `global_classes` / `global_variables` JSON.\n\n## One-shot execution path (default — use this unless told otherwise)\n\nOne-shot from a screenshot, URL, or description follows exactly **seven** steps. **Do not emit Elementor JSON** until **Step 5** (convert draft → schema): that requires **Step 3** (`HTML_DRAFT` + `CSS_DRAFT`) complete and **Step 4** satisfied (user approval **or** the brief explicitly says \"go ahead\" / \"skip approval\" / equivalent).\n\n**Step 0 — Discovery (mandatory; emit `DISCOVERY` before the brief)**\n\nFor each discovery topic, walk this source-resolution order and stop at the first hit:\n\n1. MCP `elementor://...` resource, when `user-elementor-mcp-server` is healthy and exposes the URI.\n2. Workspace dump at `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/discovery/<topic>.json`.\n3. wp-env probe via `validator/` or `import.sh` if a future hook exists.\n4. Skill-baked default documented here or in `reference.md`.\n\nIf nothing hits, use the default and add the topic to `discovery_gaps`.\n\nDiscovery topics:\n- `context/general` → `{ pro_active: bool, elementor_version: str, postId: number|null }`. Default: `{ pro_active: false, elementor_version: \"0.4\", postId: null }`.\n- `widgets/available` → list of `{ type, version, is_container }`. Default: `e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, `e-tabs`, `e-tab`, `e-tabs-menu`, `e-tabs-content-area`, `e-tab-content`, `e-svg`, `e-divider`, `e-youtube`. Do not emit a widget tag not in this list.\n- `widgets/schema/{type}` → per-widget settings schema + `llm_guidance`. Default: the canonical content-key table below.\n- `styles/schema/{category}` → PropValue shapes per style category. Default: the \"Correct PropValue shapes for common style properties\" block below.\n- `global-variables` → map of `id → { id, type, label, value }`. Default: empty map; every brand-token need becomes a `create` row in the companion payload.\n- `global-classes` → map of `id → { id, label, variants }`. Default: empty map; every catalog entry becomes a `create` row in the companion payload.\n- `breakpoints/list` → list of enabled breakpoint ids. Default: `[desktop, tablet, mobile]`.\n- `interactions/schema` → only fetched when the brief calls for interactions. Default: free-tier subset from `reference.md`.\n- `design_guidelines` → read `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md` first; if missing, read `design-guidelines.md` at the workspace root; if both missing, rely on the brief.\n\n**Step 1 — Extract brief (mandatory; output these 9 lines before Step 3 `HTML_DRAFT`)**\n\n```\nREFERENCE_TYPE: screenshot | url | description\nLOCALE: he-IL+RTL | en-US+LTR | …\nPAGE_TYPE: ecommerce-home | landing | section-only | other:<name>\nSECTIONS: [ordered list, max 8, one line each]\nMUST_HAVE_WIDGETS: [e-image, e-button, e-heading, …]\nAPPROXIMATE_COUNTS: { category_icons: 16, promo_tiles_row1: 6, … }\nBRAND_COLORS: { primary: \"#hex\", accent: \"#hex\", cta: \"#hex\", neutral: \"#hex\" }\nOUTPUT_TARGET: db-inject (default) | template-import\nPERSISTENCE_TARGET: current-page (default) | new-page\nDESIGN_GUIDELINES: inline | <path> | none\n```\n\nDefault: `OUTPUT_TARGET: db-inject` unless the user explicitly says \"template import\".\nDefault: `PERSISTENCE_TARGET: current-page` unless the user explicitly asks to create a new page.\n\nOutput these blocks before `HTML_DRAFT` (Step 3):\n\n```\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { context: mcp|dump|probe|default, variables: ..., classes: ..., ... }\n  pro_active: true | false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, ...]\n  variables: { reuse: [{id, label, type}...], create: [{label, type, value}...] }\n  classes:   { reuse: [{id, label}...],         create: [{label, source: catalog-id}...] }\n  design_guidelines_source: inline | <path> | none\n  discovery_gaps: [topic names that fell through to skill-baked default; empty when every topic resolved]\n```\n\nIn the current workspace, the healthy no-source path is explicit (ship `design-guidelines.md` in-repo so `design_guidelines` resolves without MCP):\n\n```\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { all: default }\n  pro_active: false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, e-paragraph, e-button, e-image, e-tabs, ...]\n  variables: { reuse: [], create: [{label: \"brand-primary\", type: \"global-color-variable\", value: \"#...\"}, ...] }\n  classes:   { reuse: [], create: [{label: \"section-wrap\", source: section-wrap}, ...] }\n  design_guidelines_source: .cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md\n  discovery_gaps: [global-variables, global-classes, context/general]\n```\n\n```\nDESIGN_SYSTEM:\n  catalog:\n    section-wrap:    { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"...\" }\n    content-wrap:    { kind: ..., ref: ..., props_summary: \"...\" }\n    heading-display: { kind: ..., ref: ..., props_summary: \"...\" }\n    heading-section: { kind: ..., ref: ..., props_summary: \"...\" }\n    body-text:       { ... }\n    body-small:      { ... }\n    cta-primary:     { ... }\n    cta-ghost:       { ... }\n    card-surface:    { ... }\n    link-muted:      { ... }\n  tree_class_usage_target: ≥ 95% of containers + ≥ 95% of styled widgets must reference a catalog entry\n```\n\n**When `REFERENCE_TYPE: description` (no screenshot or URL):** The output will be lower-fidelity. To compensate:\n- Ask the user for a screenshot or reference URL before proceeding, **unless they said to go ahead**.\n- Apply the design philosophy section (dominant color, weight contrast, asymmetric grids) even for `ecommerce-home`.\n- For each `e-image` in the tree, supply a thematic Unsplash URL (e.g. `https://images.unsplash.com/photo-<id>?w=800&h=600&fit=crop`) matched to the content (flowers, products, icons). Do not leave `url` empty.\n\n**Step 2 — Select PAGE_TYPE playbook** (see \"Page-type playbooks\" below) and confirm section list matches playbook order. Do not invent sections not in the playbook unless the brief demands it. Apply **creativity gates** from \"Design philosophy\" and the **Slop ban list** (rhythm, asymmetry, domain-specific copy) while respecting playbook structure—especially for `ecommerce-home`, where row order and catalog refs are primary.\n\n**Step 2.5 — Design system synthesis (mandatory; emit `DESIGN_SYSTEM` before `HTML_DRAFT`)**\n\nFrom discovery + brief, produce a small reusable class catalog: about **10–15** entries for a full page (hard cap **15** total class names in the draft), **5–7** for a section-only brief (hard cap **7**). Each class entry is either `reuse` (`{ kind: \"class\", id: \"gc_xyz1\", label: \"heading-primary\" }`) from `elementor://global-classes`, or `create` (`{ kind: \"class\", label: \"card-elevated\", props: {...} }`) emitted into the companion payload. Variables follow the same `reuse`/`create` split.\n\n**Catalog completeness (mandatory):** If the same visual treatment appears on **2+** nodes in the HTML draft, it **must** become exactly **one** catalog entry; duplicate CSS blobs for the same role are forbidden.\n\nCatalog must include at minimum: `section-wrap`, `content-wrap`, `heading-display`, `heading-section`, `body-text`, `body-small`, `cta-primary`, `cta-ghost`, `card-surface`, `link-muted`, plus any extra heading level classes the brief actually uses (e.g. `heading-primary` for h3-only pages). Add more only when 2+ elements share the treatment.\n\n**Step 3 — HTML/CSS DRAFT (mandatory; inline only — never write draft files to disk)**\n\nAfter `DESIGN_SYSTEM`, emit a structural draft **in the assistant reply only** before any Elementor JSON. Do **not** save `<slug>.draft.html` or similar into the workspace.\n\nRequired emission shape — emit **three** labeled parts in order (each part may use its own fenced block):\n\n1. **`HTML_DRAFT:`** then a ` ```html ` fence: semantic structure (e.g. `<section>`), one major block per playbook row / section; use only catalog class names on elements.\n2. **`CSS_DRAFT:`** then a ` ```css ` fence: one rule block (or grouped rules) per `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog` entry referenced in the HTML.\n3. **`DRAFT_SELF_CHECK:`** then at most **3** bullets covering: section order vs playbook; every HTML class has a catalog entry + CSS rule; any **Slop ban list** violation. **Plus a required creativity-gate bullet:** name one structural choice that distinguishes this draft from a generic template—if you cannot name one, **redo** `HTML_DRAFT` / `CSS_DRAFT` before continuing.\n\nIllustrative layout (replace `…` with real brief content):\n\n````markdown\nHTML_DRAFT:\n```html\n<section class=\"section-wrap utility-strip\">…</section>\n<section class=\"section-wrap hero-band\">\n  <div class=\"hero-media\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"…\" /></div>\n  <div class=\"hero-copy\">\n    <h1 class=\"heading-display\">…</h1>\n    <p class=\"body-text\">…</p>\n    <a class=\"cta-primary\" href=\"#\">…</a>\n  </div>\n</section>\n```\n\nCSS_DRAFT:\n```css\n.section-wrap { /* … */ }\n.hero-band { display: flex; align-items: stretch; min-height: 20rem; /* … */ }\n.heading-display { /* … */ }\n.cta-primary { /* … */ }\n```\n\nDRAFT_SELF_CHECK:\n- …\n- **Creativity gate:** …\n````\n\nDraft rules:\n\n- Every `class=\"…\"` token on HTML elements must match a **label** in `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog` (one-to-one; no ad-hoc class names).\n- Every catalog class used in HTML must have a matching rule in `CSS_DRAFT` (no orphan classes, no missing rules).\n- No inline `style=\"\"` in HTML. No `#id` selectors in CSS. No utility-class explosion—stay within the catalog size caps above.\n- Put **layout** in CSS (`display`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap`, etc.) so the draft mirrors the V4 \"layout-in-styles\" discipline.\n\n**Step 4 — Approval gate**\n\nIf the user did **not** explicitly allow proceeding without review (\"go ahead\", \"skip approval\", \"no need to approve the draft\", or equivalent), **stop after `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK`** and ask for confirmation or edits to the draft. **Do not emit** the V4 JSON tree until the user approves (or the brief already contained go-ahead).\n\n**Step 5 — Convert draft → element tree (schema emission)** — Map draft structure to V4 nodes (`e-flexbox`, `e-heading`, …). Map each `CSS_DRAFT` rule to the corresponding catalog entry's `props` (companion `create` or reused global). Map each HTML `class` list to `settings.classes.value`. Then use the canonical output shape for the chosen `OUTPUT_TARGET`, layout-in-styles rule, widget content key table, and pattern recipes — all defined below. **Global classes carry almost all visual/layout props;** local element `styles` only for documented one-offs (see \"Styling layers\").\n\n**Step 6 — Apply pattern recipes** for every non-trivial UI pattern (circle tile, promo strip, hero, search bar).\n\n**Step 7 — Validate, companion-payload, pre-handoff checklist, then hand off to `validate-elementor-page`.** When the catalog contains any `create` entry, emit a sibling `<slug>.companion.json` next to the template using the shape from `reference.md` → \"Companion primitives\" → \"Companion payload shape\". Always emit it; never silently drop a `create` entry. Run `php validate-elementor-json.php <output.json>` from the workspace root; fix every reported error (element path + prop name) and re-run until it passes. Then check every checklist box below. Do not deliver without validation passing and every box checked. After validation passes, chain into the `validate-elementor-page` skill (which imports the JSON into wp-env, takes a screenshot, and runs the publish cycle) before declaring success.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output shapes\n\n| `OUTPUT_TARGET` | Root shape | Container `elType` | Layout properties live in | `settings` holds |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `db-inject` (default) | bare `[{…}]` array | `\"e-flexbox\"` or `\"e-div-block\"` (no `widgetType` field) | `styles[id].variants[0].props` | `classes` ($$type: classes) + widget content keys |\n| `template-import` | envelope `{ version, title, type, page_settings, content: […] }` | same | same | same |\n\n**Hard rule:** For every `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block`, the properties `display`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap` MUST go in `styles[localStyleId].variants[0].props`. They must NOT be placed only in `settings`. `settings` holds `classes` and widget-specific content keys only.\n\nThe template-import envelope shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"0.4\",\n  \"title\":   \"Page — <name>\",\n  \"type\":    \"page\",\n  \"page_settings\": {},\n  \"content\": [ /* root nodes */ ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Widget content key table (canonical — no alternatives)\n\n| Widget | Content key in `settings` | `$$type` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `e-heading` | `title` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-paragraph` | `paragraph` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-button` | `text` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-image` | `image` | `image` (with nested `src` → `image-src` → `{ id, url }`) |\n| `e-tab` | `label` | `html-v3` |\n\n`html-v3` shape — **this is an object, not a plain string**. A bare string value is silently rejected and the widget falls back to its default placeholder text (or empty):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Your text here</p>\" },\n    \"children\": []\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe validator (`validate-elementor-json.php`) now runs each widget's real `define_props_schema()` over its `settings`, so passing a bare-string `html-v3` fails validation with `settings.<key>: invalid_value`. If you see that, you wrote the old wrong shape — fix the value to the object form above.\n\n`image` shape (correct — used by the good repo output):\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"image\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"src\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"image-src\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"id\": null,\n        \"url\": { \"$$type\": \"url\", \"value\": \"https://example.com/image.jpg\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"full\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Wrong `image` shape (do not use):**\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"image\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"image-src\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"url\" },\n    \"url\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThese are the only correct keys. Do not use `label` for buttons, `text` for paragraphs, or bare `string` for any of these. The anchor snippet in this file and the examples in `examples.md` have been updated to use these keys.\n\n### Link PropValue (used by `e-button`, `e-image`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`)\n\nThe `link` settings key is a `Link_Prop_Type`, **not** an `object`. Real shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"link\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"destination\":   { \"$$type\": \"url\",     \"value\": \"/signup\" },\n    \"isTargetBlank\": { \"$$type\": \"boolean\", \"value\": false }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nOptional inner field: `tag` (`{ \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"a\" }` or `\"button\"`).\n\n**Wrong (commonly seen in older snippets — fails settings validation, link silently drops):**\n\n```json\n{ \"$$type\": \"object\", \"value\": { \"url\": {...}, \"is_external\": {...} } }\n```\n\n---\n\n## The V4 element tree — node shape\n\nEvery node in `content[]` (and recursively in `elements[]`) has:\n\n- `id` — stable string id you generate (uuid-like). Required, unique within file.\n- `elType` — **depends on the element type** (see table below). Never use a single blanket value.\n- `widgetType` — **only present when `elType === \"widget\"`**. Omit entirely for container elements.\n- `editor_settings` — `{ title: \"Hero Section\" }` — always set.\n- `settings` — record of PropValues for widget-specific content keys (see table above) and `classes`.\n- `styles` *(optional)* — local style definitions. **All layout and visual props for containers go here.**\n- `elements` *(optional)* — child nodes. Only for widgets with `can_have_children: true`.\n- `interactions` *(optional)* — `{ version: 1, items: [...] }`.\n\n### `elType` / `widgetType` rule — critical\n\nElementor has **two separate registries**. The wrong `elType` causes `create_element_instance` to return `null` and the element silently disappears:\n\n| Element | `elType` value | `widgetType` field |\n|---|---|---|\n| `e-heading` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-heading\"` |\n| `e-paragraph` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-paragraph\"` |\n| `e-button` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-button\"` |\n| `e-image` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-image\"` |\n| `e-svg` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-svg\"` |\n| `e-divider` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-divider\"` |\n| `e-youtube` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-youtube\"` |\n| `e-flexbox` | `\"e-flexbox\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-div-block` | `\"e-div-block\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs` | `\"e-tabs\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tab` | `\"e-tab\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs-menu` | `\"e-tabs-menu\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs-content-area` | `\"e-tabs-content-area\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tab-content` | `\"e-tab-content\"` | **omit** |\n\n**Rule:** Container/structural elements use their own name as `elType` and have **no `widgetType` field**. Leaf content widgets use `elType: \"widget\"` with `widgetType: \"<name>\"`.\n\n**Never write** `{ \"elType\": \"widget\", \"widgetType\": \"e-flexbox\" }` — that node produces no output.\n\n### PropValues — the #1 source of rejections\n\nEvery value in `settings` and `styles` is a PropValue: `{ \"$$type\": \"<type>\", \"value\": <typed-value> }`. The `$$type` must match exactly what the widget's schema says. Example:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"font-size\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"size\",\n    \"value\": {\n      \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 3.5 },\n      \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNever guess `$$type`. Fetch the widget schema or style-category schema.\n\n### Styling layers\n\n1. **Global classes (DEFAULT — almost everything).** Every container and every styled widget references one or more classes from `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog`. Reuse existing `gc_*` ids when discovery found a match; otherwise the catalog entry is emitted as a `create` row and goes into the companion payload. **Layout and visual props live on those global class definitions** (companion snapshot or site reuse)—not duplicated as ad-hoc locals. The pre-handoff checklist enforces **≥ 95%** catalog linkage on containers and styled widgets.\n2. **Local element `styles` (rare escape hatch).** Reserved **only** for documented one-offs that truly apply to **exactly one** node in the entire tree (e.g. asymmetric hero offset, single decorative overlay, one-of-one positioning tweak). **Mandatory justification:** append a one-line reason to `editor_settings.title` (e.g. `\"Hero column — local: asymmetric offset\"`) **or** note `local_style_reason: …` in the same assistant turn before JSON. If the same props would apply to 2+ nodes in the HTML draft or final tree, **lift to a catalog entry**—no exceptions.\n3. **`custom_css`.** Escape hatch only.\n\n### Variants — responsive and state\n\nEach style definition is a list of variants with `meta: { breakpoint, state }` and a `props` bag. Only use breakpoint ids from `elementor://breakpoints/list`.\n\n### Variables — referenced by id\n\nUse the variable's id from `elementor://global-variables`, never the label:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"color\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\",\n    \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_a1b2\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### V4 Global Classes & Variables Database and Import Mechanism\n\nTo ensure that V4 global classes and global variables are correctly registered and persist layout/styles on the target site:\n\n1. **V4 Database Storage and Architecture**:\n   - **Global Classes**: Stored as custom WordPress post types of type `e_global_class`. Each class has standard fields like post title (holding the class label/name), with post metadata like `_elementor_global_class_id` (the ID, e.g., `g-a1b2`) and the JSON-encoded styles definition under `_elementor_global_class_data`. The order and label-to-ID mappings are maintained under `_elementor_global_classes` and `_elementor_global_classes_labels` keys in the *active Kit's* post meta.\n   - **Global Variables**: Stored under the `_elementor_global_variables` post meta key on the *active Kit* post, representing the global variables collection.\n\n2. **Native Safe Merge and Import System**:\n   - Elementor V4 natively handles safe merging and importing of global variables and classes via the `'elementor/template_library/import/process_content'` filter (registered at priority 10 for variables and priority 20 for global classes).\n   - This native flow automatically:\n     - Extracts and parses `\"global_variables\"` and `\"global_classes\"` snapshots from the import data/envelope.\n     - Merges incoming items with existing ones on the target site by matching their `label` (using the repository's `is_matching_item()`).\n     - Safely reuses any matching label and skips duplicating it on the site.\n     - Persists any new primitives to the database (creating the necessary posts/kit meta).\n     - Dynamically rewrites all temporary class/variable IDs in the element content tree and class style properties so they point to the correct site-merged/created database IDs.\n\n3. **Placeholder Resolution on Import**:\n   - When generating templates with companion files (e.g. `<slug>.companion.json`), variables and classes are referenced using `@@label:<name>` placeholders (e.g., `@@label:brand-primary`).\n   - On import (`import.sh` / `scripts/import-elementor-data.php`), these placeholders are converted to temporary V4-compliant IDs (like `e-gv-<slug>` for variables and `g-<slug>` for classes) in both the tree and snapshots, and then passed into the native `import/process_content` filter, which merges and maps them to final site IDs seamlessly.\n\n### Container rules\n\nA widget is a container iff `llm_guidance.can_have_children === true`. Respect `allowed_child_types` and `allowed_parents`. Include `required_direct_children` (e.g. `e-tabs` requires `e-tab` children) even if the user didn't mention them.\n\n### Anchor snippet (uses correct keys)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_hero_heading\",\n  \"elType\": \"widget\",\n  \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Hero Heading\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"title\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h1>Ship faster</h1>\" },\n        \"children\": []\n      }\n    },\n    \"tag\":   { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h1\" }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"e-heading-local-1\": {\n      \"id\": \"e-heading-local-1\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"props\": {\n            \"font-size\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"size\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 4 },\n                \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIn real output, prefer **global catalog classes** for typography and layout; this snippet shows correct `html-v3` + local `styles` wiring (`\"label\": \"local\"` on each local style entry — see checklist). Avoid copying the local `font-size` pattern when a `heading-display`-class definition exists in the companion.\n\n---\n\n## Page-type playbooks\n\nSelect the matching playbook. Fill its rows from the brief. Do not invent rows not in the playbook unless the brief explicitly demands them.\n\n### `ecommerce-home`\n\nThe `Catalog refs` column lists which `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog` entries each row uses. Concrete prop values live in the catalog, not in the playbook.\n\n| # | Row purpose | `widgetType` | Child count (typical) | Layout | Catalog refs |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Utility strip (links, phone, language) | `e-flexbox` row | 3–6 `e-paragraph` or `e-button` | `flex-direction: row`, `justify-content: space-between` | `section-wrap`, `utility-strip`, `body-small`, `link-muted` |\n| 2 | Header (logo + search + account/cart) | `e-flexbox` row | logo `e-image`, search `e-flexbox`, icons row | `justify-content: space-between`, `align-items: center` | `section-wrap`, `header-row`, `logo-mark`, `search-shell`, `icon-button` |\n| 3 | Category text nav | `e-flexbox` row | 6–10 `e-button` or `e-paragraph` | `flex-direction: row`, `flex-wrap: wrap`, `gap: 0` | `nav-row`, `nav-link`, `body-small` |\n| 4 | Icon grid | outer `e-flexbox` column → inner `e-flexbox` row ×N | N circle tiles (see pattern recipes) | rows: `flex-wrap: wrap`, `justify-content: center`, `gap: 1rem` | `section-wrap`, `content-wrap`, `circle-tile`, `body-small` |\n| 5 | Hero band | `e-flexbox` row | `e-image` ~55% + `e-flexbox` column (h1, p, badge, CTA) | `align-items: stretch`, `min-height: 20rem` | `section-wrap`, `hero-band`, `hero-media`, `hero-copy`, `heading-display`, `body-text`, `cta-primary` |\n| 6 | Promo strip A | `e-flexbox` row | 4–6 equal-height tiles `e-div-block` | `flex-wrap: nowrap`, `overflow-x: auto`, `gap: 0.5rem` | `promo-strip`, `promo-card`, `promo-media`, `body-text` |\n| 7 | Promo strip B | `e-flexbox` row | 2–4 mixed-width tiles | same as A but tiles may vary `flex-basis` | `promo-strip`, `promo-card-featured`, `promo-media`, `heading-section` |\n| 8 | Legal footer bar | `e-flexbox` row | logo `e-image`, nav links `e-paragraph` ×N, copyright | `justify-content: space-between`, `align-items: center` | `footer-bar`, `logo-mark`, `link-muted`, `body-small` |\n\n### `landing`\n\nUse when `PAGE_TYPE: landing`. Free-form but sections must earn their place: capture attention → establish credibility → demonstrate value → remove objection → drive action. Resist defaulting to \"hero + three columns + testimonials + CTA\" without reason. Design philosophy details in `reference.md`.\n\n### `section-only`\n\nGenerate only the single requested section. Pick the matching row from the relevant page-type playbook for structural guidance.\n\n---\n\n## Pattern recipes\n\n### Circle category tile\n\n```\ne-flexbox (column, align-items: center, gap: 0.5rem, width: 5rem)\n  └─ e-image (fixed square, e.g. 3.5rem × 3.5rem, border-radius: 50% in styles)\n  └─ e-paragraph (\"Category Name\", text-align: center, font-size: 0.75rem)\n```\n\nNever use emoji in `e-paragraph` as an icon substitute. Use `e-icon` if available (check `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4`), or a small `e-image` SVG/PNG.\n\n### Horizontal promo strip\n\n```\ne-flexbox (row, flex-wrap: nowrap, overflow-x: auto, gap: 0.5rem)\n  └─ e-div-block ×N (flex: 0 0 auto, min-height: 12rem, overflow: hidden)\n       └─ e-image (width: 100%, height: 100%, object-fit: cover)\n       └─ e-paragraph (overlay text, position via custom_css if needed)\n```\n\n### Hero band\n\n```\ne-flexbox (row, align-items: stretch, min-height: 20rem)\n  ├─ e-image (flex: 0 0 55%, object-fit: cover)\n  └─ e-flexbox (column, flex: 1, justify-content: center, gap: 1rem, padding: 2rem)\n       ├─ e-heading (h1, brand headline)\n       ├─ e-paragraph (subhead or badge text)\n       └─ e-button (CTA — prominent color, border-radius: 0.25rem)\n```\n\n### Search bar\n\n```\ne-flexbox (row, align-items: center, border: 1px solid neutral, border-radius: 0.25rem)\n  ├─ e-image (search icon SVG, width: 1.25rem, flex-shrink: 0)\n  ├─ e-paragraph (placeholder \"חיפוש…\" or \"Search…\", flex: 1)\n  └─ e-image (mic icon SVG, width: 1.25rem, flex-shrink: 0)  ← optional\n```\n\n### Logo\n\nAlways use `e-image`, never `e-heading` text as a logo substitute.\n\n### Icons\n\n1. Check `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4` for `e-icon`.\n2. If present → use `e-icon` with the required schema keys.\n3. If absent → use a small `e-image` with an SVG or PNG src.\n4. Never use emoji in `e-paragraph` as an icon default.\n\n---\n\n## Carousel / slider decision\n\n1. Fetch `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4`.\n2. If a `e-carousel`, `e-slider`, or equivalent widget is listed → use it; fetch its schema for required children and settings keys.\n3. If absent → documented fallback:\n   - Render all slides as `e-div-block` children in an `e-flexbox` row with `overflow-x: auto`, `flex-wrap: nowrap`.\n   - Add a prev/next row below using two `e-button` widgets (`‹` / `›`).\n   - Note in a code comment that this is the static fallback pending carousel widget availability.\n   - Do not silently drop carousel visuals from the reference; the static strip is the fallback, not the absence.\n\n---\n\n## RTL and locale\n\nWhen `LOCALE` contains `RTL` or locale is `he-IL`, `ar-*`, or any RTL language:\n\n1. **Page root** — add to `page_settings`:\n   ```json\n   { \"direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rtl\" } }\n   ```\n2. **Text containers** — in styles props use `text-align: end` (not `right`) and `align-items: flex-end` where text should trail.\n3. **Prefer logical CSS** — use `padding-inline-start`, `padding-inline-end`, `margin-inline-*` instead of `left`/`right` wherever the style-schema supports them.\n4. **Hebrew copy** — wrap placeholder text in Hebrew: e.g. `<p>כותרת</p>`, `<p>טקסט תיאורי כאן</p>`.\n5. **Icon order** — in RTL rows, the logical reading order reverses; place icons on the `inline-start` side.\n\n---\n\n## Fidelity budget for one-shot\n\nThe **HTML/CSS draft (Step 3)** is the fidelity contract for structure and class-level styling intent; Step 5 JSON must **not** drift from that draft except to satisfy V4 schema/widget constraints (then note the delta in `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK` follow-up or the handoff note).\n\n**MUST reproduce (structure):**\n- Section order matching PAGE_TYPE playbook\n- Hebrew / locale copy placeholders\n- One `e-image` widget per distinct visual in the reference (hero image, promo tile image, category icon, logo)\n- CTA button present where reference shows one\n- Promo tile count matching `APPROXIMATE_COUNTS`\n- Footer bar present\n\n**MAY approximate (polish):**\n- Exact carousel motion / transitions\n- Real brand asset URLs — use a thematically relevant Unsplash placeholder URL (e.g. `https://images.unsplash.com/photo-<id>?w=800&h=600&fit=crop`) so the page renders visually. Never leave `url` as an empty string `\"\"` — an empty src results in a broken image placeholder.\n- Pixel-perfect widths and font sizes\n- Actual font file references\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Emoji characters as icon substitutes in `e-paragraph`\n- `e-heading` text as logo\n- Flex layout properties placed only in `settings` (must be in `styles` / global class props)\n- Skip `e-image` widgets for visuals that exist in the reference\n- Invent \"testimonials\" or unrelated sections not in the playbook or brief\n- Use `6–10rem` vertical gaps as a default for ecommerce rows (use `0–1rem` row gaps; section padding `2–3rem`)\n- Drift from the approved `HTML_DRAFT` / `CSS_DRAFT` without schema-forced cause and a short note\n\n---\n\n## Pre-handoff checklist (run before delivering)\n\nCheck every box. Do not deliver until all pass.\n\n- [ ] Output is a bare `[{…}]` array (db-inject) unless user explicitly requested template-import\n- [ ] Every `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block` node uses `elType: \"e-flexbox\"` / `elType: \"e-div-block\"` with **no `widgetType`** field\n- [ ] Every leaf widget (`e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, …) uses `elType: \"widget\"` with the correct `widgetType`\n- [ ] Every `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block` has flex layout props in `styles[id].variants[0].props`, not only in `settings`\n- [ ] Every text widget uses the correct content key + `html-v3` (see widget content key table)\n- [ ] Every entry in the `styles` map of an element (local style) has its `\"label\"` field set exactly to `\"local\"`. Missing or custom labels on element-level styles prevent Elementor from recognizing them as local, which leads to double compilation and breaks edit/save cycles.\n- [ ] `DISCOVERY` block was emitted; `discovery_gaps` is empty OR each gap is justified in a note.\n- [ ] `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog` was emitted; every `create` entry has a matching row in the companion payload JSON (`<slug>.companion.json`), and every `reuse` entry's id was returned by `elementor://global-classes` or `elementor://global-variables`.\n- [ ] In companion snapshots and templates, all global variable references are plain string IDs, e.g., `{\"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-primary\"}` (NOT nested with `{\"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": ...}`).\n- [ ] In companion snapshots and templates, `line-height` style properties use the `size` PropType, e.g. `{\"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": {\"size\": 1.2, \"unit\": \"em\"}}` (NOT `{\"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.2}`). Incorrect formats cause the Elementor V4 parser to silently drop all global classes.\n- [ ] Every node with a `styles` entry has its style ID present in `settings.classes.value` (never `[]`).\n- [ ] At least **95%** of containers and at least **95%** of **styled** widgets reference a catalog entry via `settings.classes.value`. Any remaining nodes use catalog coverage for every repeated treatment; local `styles` appear only on **one-off** nodes (same treatment on **exactly one** node).\n- [ ] Every node that still uses **local** `styles` includes a justification (see \"Styling layers\": suffix on `editor_settings.title` or `local_style_reason` in the same turn) and that treatment does not repeat elsewhere in the tree.\n- [ ] `HTML_DRAFT`, `CSS_DRAFT`, and `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK` were emitted before JSON; user approved the draft **or** the brief explicitly allowed go-ahead / skip approval.\n- [ ] At least one section reflects intentional design variety: **asymmetric grid** OR **non-uniform vertical rhythm** across sections OR a **distinctive type pairing**—and the choice is justified by the brief (not generic filler).\n- [ ] No `color` PropType value uses a CSS keyword (e.g. `\"transparent\"`) — only hex strings are valid. Omit the `background` prop instead of setting color to transparent.\n- [ ] Every distinct visual from the reference has a corresponding `e-image` (or `e-icon`) widget in the tree\n- [ ] Section count and order matches the PAGE_TYPE playbook rows covered by the brief\n- [ ] `page_settings` includes `direction: rtl` for RTL locales\n- [ ] No flex properties appear only in `settings` (they would render as broken/overlapping layout)\n- [ ] No emoji characters used as icon substitutes\n- [ ] Typography uses proper proportional `line-height` (e.g. `1.2em` to `1.35em` for headings, `1.5em` to `1.6em` for paragraphs) to prevent cramping/overlaps. Never hardcode absolute line-heights that are smaller than the font-size (such as `1.3rem` on `2.25rem` headings).\n- [ ] Every text-carrying widget (`e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`) sets an intentional `font-family` stack — either a distinctive webfont pairing aligned to the brief or an explicit system stack (`system-ui`, `-apple-system`, `Segoe UI`, sans-serif) — so running text never falls back to browser-default Times or unnamed generic serif.\n- [ ] Secondary, ghost, or outlined buttons have high Legibility: they must NOT blend completely into the section's background (e.g., set transparent or distinct contrasting backgrounds, outline border-color, and text-color to preserve premium contrast).\n- [ ] Content columns, text CTA containers, and centered sections have professional `max-width` limits (e.g. `600px` to `700px` for text sections, `1140px` to `1200px` for card grids) and generous vertical padding (`4rem` to `8rem`) for an airy, premium look.\n- [ ] Cards, testimonials, and section tiles have modern design depth using elegant rounded corners (`border-radius: 0.5rem` to `1.25rem`) and soft, premium box-shadows (such as `0 10px 30px -3px rgba(0,0,0,0.04), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02)`).\n- [ ] `php validate-elementor-json.php <file.json>` passes (uses real Elementor `Style_Schema` + `Props_Parser` from `~/Dev/elementor`)\n\n---\n\n## Mode selection\n\n**Single-shot** — Use by default for any brief with ≤ 8 sections. Follow the **seven-step** one-shot path above (through HTML/CSS draft, approval when required, then JSON).\n\n**Iterative** — Use when the page is large, the brief is ambiguous, or a single-shot validation pass surfaces errors spanning > 2 distinct nodes. Still emit **`DESIGN_SYSTEM` → `HTML_DRAFT` / `CSS_DRAFT` / `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK`** for the slice you are building (or the full page outline) before JSON for that slice. Then: skeleton JSON (root containers + class refs), fill sections, then interactions.\n\n---\n\n## Interactions\n\nAdd sparingly — pick 2–3 high-impact moments (hero reveal, primary CTA, a featured section's scroll-in). Hard cap: 3 interactions per element.\n\nEach interaction item carries: `trigger` (`load`, `scrollIn`; Pro adds `hover`, `click`, `scrollOn`, `scrollOut`), `animation.effect` (`fade`, `slide`, `scale`; Pro adds `custom`), optional `direction` (required for `slide`), `timing_config.duration/delay` in ms, `config.easing` (`easeIn` free; Pro adds more), and optional `breakpoints` exclusion list.\n\nGate Pro-only triggers/effects/easings behind a check of `elementor://context/general`.\n\n---\n\n## Design philosophy (applies to every `PAGE_TYPE`)\n\nApply creative design intent for **all** page types: one dominant color, one accent, tinted neutrals, typography with strong weight contrast (aim for **3×+** headline-to-body ratio where the brief allows). Vary section heights and widths; avoid `100vh` on every section; prefer **asymmetric** grids and splits when they carry the same information as symmetric ones. Prescriptive detail in `design-guidelines.md`; vocabulary in `reference.md`.\n\nFor **`ecommerce-home`**, playbook row order and catalog refs are **primary**—do not drop or reorder rows—but still apply tokens, rhythm, and anti-slop copy (domain-specific placeholders, varied `padding-block` per row role).\n\n### Slop ban list (non-exhaustive)\n\n- No three-equal-column \"features\" rows unless the brief explicitly asks for that pattern.\n- No generic filler copy (`Lorem ipsum`, \"Get started today\", \"Trusted by thousands\", \"Join millions\", etc.). Placeholders must sound like the brief's real domain and audience.\n- No section that only fills vertical space—every block earns a job: **attention → credibility → value → objection → action** (skip beats the brief does not need).\n- No identical vertical rhythm on every section—vary `padding-block` / band height by section role.\n- No default symmetric 50/50 split when **7/5**, **8/4**, or **9/3** (or similar) carries the same content with more interest.\n- No uniform `border-radius: 0.5rem` on every surface—define a small **radius scale** (e.g. sharp / `0.25rem` / `1rem`) and assign by role (chips vs cards vs hero).\n\n### Creativity gate\n\nBefore locking the HTML/CSS draft, ensure **at least one** deliberate structural or compositional choice reads as **non-template** (asymmetric layout, unexpected but justified section order tweak allowed by the brief, distinctive typographic ladder, editorial spacing). If everything looks like a default SaaS landing, **redo** the draft.\n\n---\n\n## On import errors\n\nIf the user imports and gets a rejection, the editor reports the offending node path. Fix only that node — never regenerate the whole tree. Common fixes: wrong `$$type` → look up style schema; unknown class/variable id → you used a label or fabricated id; missing required child → add it; Pro-only feature on non-Pro → substitute.\n\n---\n\n## Correct PropValue shapes for common style properties\n\nUse these exact shapes. Wrong `$$type` is the #1 silent failure.\n\n**Background color** (use `background` prop, not `background-color`):\n```json\n{\n  \"background\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"background\",\n    \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#1a1a2e\" } }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Text color** (use `color` prop):\n```json\n{ \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" } }\n```\n\n**Font size** (`size` inner fields are plain primitives, not nested PropValues):\n```json\n{\n  \"font-size\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"size\",\n    \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Border radius**:\n```json\n{\n  \"border-radius\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"size\",\n    \"value\": { \"size\": 0.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Padding** (use `padding` with `dimensions` type — not `padding-block-start` / `padding-inline-*`):\n```json\n{\n  \"padding\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"dimensions\",\n    \"value\": {\n      \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n      \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n      \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n      \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Failure modes (high-frequency)\n\n- **Wrong or Missing `label` on local style definitions** — every entry in an element's `styles` map represents a local style and **must** have its `\"label\"` field set exactly to `\"local\"`. Elementor's style processor expects `\"label\": \"local\"` to match element-level styles on import/flattening; missing or custom labels (like `\"label\": \"pc_logo_style\"`) prevent Elementor from recognizing them as local, which leads to duplicate stylesheet generation, overlaps, and broken edit/save cycles. (Global classes in companion snapshots or catalogs, on the other hand, should have descriptive class names as their labels).\n- **`transparent` keyword in `color` PropType** — Elementor's `color` type only accepts hex strings. Using the CSS keyword `\"transparent\"` causes a schema error at load. Omit the `background` prop entirely to leave the background unset (which is equivalent to transparent).\n- **Wrong `html-v3` value shape** — `{$$type:\"html-v3\", value:\"<p>...</p>\"}` (plain string) is rejected by `Html_V3_Prop_Type::validate_value()`. The widget falls back to its default placeholder (\"This is a title\", \"Type your paragraph here\", \"Click here\") or empty. **Correct shape:** `value: { content: { $$type:\"string\", value:\"...\" }, children: [] }`.\n- **Wrong `link` PropValue** — `$$type: \"object\"` with `url`/`is_external` is the older/wrong shape. Real `Link_Prop_Type` uses `$$type: \"link\"` with inner `destination` (Url PV) and `isTargetBlank` (Boolean PV). Links silently disappear on import if you use the wrong shape.\n- **Wrong `elType` for containers** — `{ \"elType\": \"widget\", \"widgetType\": \"e-flexbox\" }` produces a silent empty output. Containers (`e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-tabs`, etc.) must use `elType: \"e-flexbox\"` with **no `widgetType`**. See the elType/widgetType table above.\n- **Flex layout in `settings` only** — breaks container layout. Move `display`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap` to `styles[id].variants[0].props`.\n- **Wrong content key** — `label` on `e-button` (correct: `text`), `text` on `e-paragraph` (correct: `paragraph`), `title` with `$$type: \"string\"` on `e-heading` (correct: `html-v3`).\n- **`tag` on `e-heading` outside h1..h6** — `span`, `p`, etc. are rejected. If you need wordmark-style text, use `e-paragraph`, not `e-heading`.\n- **Wrong `$$type`** — `{$$type:\"string\", value:\"#fff\"}` for a color. Look up the style schema for `color` category, or use the PropValue shapes table above.\n- **Wrong `size` inner shape** — `size` PropValue inner `value` must be `{ \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" }` (plain number + string). Nested `{ \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 }` fails `Props_Parser` validation.\n- **Unknown style prop names** — e.g. `background-color`, `padding-block-start`, `overflow-x`. Use schema-valid names only (`background`, `padding`, `overflow`). Run `php validate-elementor-json.php` to catch these.\n- **Wrong `background` shape** — using `background-color` with `$$type: \"color\"` may be rejected. Use `background` with `$$type: \"background\"` containing a `color` sub-key (see shapes table above).\n- **Wrong `e-image` schema** — using `{ \"image-src\": { \"$$type\": \"string\" } }` is the old/incorrect shape. Use the `src → image-src → { id, url }` shape from the widget content key table.\n- **Empty image URLs** — `\"url\": \"\"` produces broken image placeholders. Always provide a thematic Unsplash URL when no real asset exists.\n- **Referencing fabricated class/variable ids** — fetch the resources, use real ids.\n- **Emoji icons** — never default to emoji; use `e-icon` or `e-image`.\n- **Wrong `e-tabs` child structure** — (2026-05-24, landing-page-event) `e-tab` nodes placed **directly** under `e-tabs` (with content nested inside each `e-tab`) produce Alpine JS runtime errors and broken tab behavior. `e-tabs` requires exactly two child containers: (1) `e-tabs-menu` containing the `e-tab` trigger buttons, and (2) `e-tabs-content-area` containing `e-tab-content` panels. Each `e-tab` trigger must have a nested `e-paragraph` child for the label text (not `settings.label` — that key is unknown on `e-tab`). Each `e-tab-content` panel holds the actual section content and needs `settings.tab-id` pointing to its `e-tab`'s id. Concretely: `e-tabs → [e-tabs-menu → [e-tab → [e-paragraph]], e-tabs-content-area → [e-tab-content (settings.tab-id) → [content…]]]`.\n- **`e-tabs` runtime race on Elementor 4.0.7** — (2026-05-25, landing-page-event, see `validated-outputs/bad/landing-page-event.why.md`) even with the correct `e-tabs → [e-tabs-menu(e-tab*), e-tabs-content-area(e-tab-content*)]` shape, atomic-widgets' `tabs-handler.js` registers `Alpine.data('eTabs<id>', ...)` after Alpine evaluates `x-data=\"eTabs<id>\"` on the node. Result: 8 page errors per tab group, tabs not interactive at runtime. JSON validator and import are clean; the failure is script load-order. Action: treat `e-tabs` as known-broken on the front URL. Prefer an `e-flexbox` column with stacked sub-sections in its place. If `e-tabs` is genuinely required, mark the deliverable as expected-fail on the front-URL Alpine check.\n- **Missing `required_direct_children`** — `e-tabs` without `e-tab` items is rejected.\n- **Pro-only interactions on non-Pro site** — gate with `elementor://context/general`.\n- **Regenerating the whole tree on one error** — fix the node at the reported path only.\n- **Equal-width card row stacks vertically instead of side-by-side** — (2026-05-25, pricing-section, run-20260525-101009) a row container with `display: flex` + `flex-wrap: wrap` containing N \"equal\" cards (e.g. 3 pricing tiers) renders as a single full-width column when the child cards have no explicit `width` / `flex-basis`. Each child claims its intrinsic content width (~100% of the row), wraps onto its own line, and the 3-up grid collapses. `flex: 1` is **not** the default on `e-div-block`/`e-flexbox` children. **Fix:** add an explicit `width` to each card's style-class `props`, sized to `≈ (100 − total_gap%) / N`. Use the canonical `size` PropValue shape. For a 3-up row with small gaps: `\"width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 30, \"unit\": \"%\" } }` on each card, bump the elevated/middle card to `32%` if the brief calls it out. Verified against the prior-good `validated-outputs/good/pricing-section.json` which uses the same pattern.\n- **Ghost / outlined `e-button` renders filled with the theme default** — (2026-05-25, hero-section + newsletter-cta-section, run-20260525-101009) a secondary / ghost / outlined button drawn without a `background` prop renders with the theme's solid default (often brand-primary or blue) because the schema's `color` PropType rejects `\"transparent\"` (separate documented failure) AND simply omitting `background` lets the theme stylesheet win. **Fix:** when you intend a ghost button, set `background` to a real hex matching the section background (`#ffffff` for a white section), pair it with a visible `border` (`border-width: 1px`, `border-style: solid`, `border-color: <accent>`), and set the `color` prop to the accent so the label is readable. Never assume omission = transparent.\n- **Styles defined but not applied on `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block`** — (2026-05-24, promo-strip-section; 2026-05-24, newsletter-cta-section; 2026-05-24, pricing-section) styles are defined in the `styles` object but `settings.classes.value` is left as `[]`. The styles are never rendered. Every node (containers AND widgets) that has a `styles` entry **must** reference the style ID in `settings.classes.value`, e.g. `\"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"nl_section_outer_style\"] }`. Without this link, CSS classes are compiled but never assigned to the rendered HTML element — background colors, flex-direction, padding, borders all silently fail. This applies to `e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, and all other node types. Symptom: all child elements appear on one horizontal row regardless of `flex-direction: column` — identical to the style never being written at all.\n- **Local-styles explosion** — emitting N near-identical local `styles` blobs (one per container, card, or button) instead of a single reusable catalog class. Symptoms: huge JSON, duplicate CSS class names, divergence between visually identical cards, expensive editor save. Lift any treatment that appears on 2+ nodes into a `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog` entry and reference it via `settings.classes.value`. The checklist targets **≥ 95%** catalog linkage for containers and styled widgets.\n\n---\n\n## See also\n\n- `design-guidelines.md` — author-time design system for JSON (palette, type, motion, spatial intent, anti-slop for structure/tokens).\n- `reference.md` — expanded vocabulary, resource response shapes, template-import envelope, companion-primitives flow.\n- `examples.md` — corrected trees illustrating nesting + required children, three-layer styling with variants, variables + interactions, and a complete importable template. All examples use the canonical widget content keys.\n";

export const referenceDocs = "# Reference — V4 page generation\n\nExpanded vocabulary from `SKILL.md`, sample response shape per resource, the template-import envelope, and the companion-primitives flow.\n\n## Discovery output spec\n\nThe one-shot flow always emits `DISCOVERY` and `DESIGN_SYSTEM` before the element tree. Resolve each topic in this order and record the winning source: MCP `elementor://...` resource, workspace dump at `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/discovery/<topic>.json`, wp-env probe, then skill-baked default. If a topic falls through to default, list it in `discovery_gaps`; do not hide missing discovery.\n\n**Topic `design_guidelines`:** read `design-guidelines.md` under `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/` first, then `<workspace-root>/design-guidelines.md`; if neither exists, use the brief’s `DESIGN_GUIDELINES:` line and inline philosophy from `SKILL.md`.\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { context: mcp|dump|probe|default, variables: ..., classes: ..., ... }\n  pro_active: true | false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, ...]\n  variables:\n    reuse:  [{ id: var_a1b2, label: brand-primary, type: global-color-variable }]\n    create: [{ label: brand-primary, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#0F766E\" }]\n  classes:\n    reuse:  [{ id: gc_xyz1, label: heading-primary }]\n    create: [{ label: section-wrap, source: section-wrap }]\n  design_guidelines_source: inline | <path> | none\n  discovery_gaps: [global-variables, global-classes]\n```\n\n```yaml\nDESIGN_SYSTEM:\n  catalog:\n    section-wrap:    { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"outer section spacing\" }\n    content-wrap:    { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"max-width centered column\" }\n    heading-display: { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"hero headline\" }\n    body-text:       { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"default paragraph\" }\n    cta-primary:     { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"filled primary CTA\" }\n    cta-ghost:       { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"outlined secondary CTA\" }\n    card-surface:    { kind: create|reuse, ref: <label-or-id>, props_summary: \"shared card surface\" }\n  tree_class_usage_target: \">= 60% containers and >= 50% widgets reference catalog classes\"\n```\n\nWhen `source_resolution: { all: default }`, `variables.reuse` and `classes.reuse` are empty, and every required token/class becomes a `create` row in the companion payload. When a live source returns matching labels or compatible variants, flip those catalog entries to `reuse` and omit them from the companion payload.\n\n## Expanded vocabulary, by resource\n\nThese URIs describe the expected response shape. When no live source exposes them, treat the documented JSON as the data contract and supply it via a workspace dump under `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/discovery/` or fall back to skill-baked defaults.\n\nEach resource answers a specific question. Fetch only when you have the question.\n\n### `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4`\n\nLists every V4 (Atomic) widget registered on the site. Confirm a widget tag exists before emitting it.\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"type\": \"e-flexbox\",   \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Flex container\", \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-div-block\", \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Block container\", \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-heading\",   \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Heading\", \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-paragraph\", \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Paragraph\", \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-button\",    \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Button\",  \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-image\",     \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Image\",   \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-tabs\",      \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Tabs\",    \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-tab\",       \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Tab item\",\"is_container\": true }\n]\n```\n\nIf a widget you want isn't here, ask the user; don't substitute silently.\n\n### `elementor://widgets/schema/{widgetType}`\n\nWidget's `settings` schema plus `llm_guidance`. Read before writing any `settings` block for a widget you haven't used yet in this session.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"title\": { \"kind\": \"union\", \"prop_types\": { \"string\": { \"kind\": \"string\" } } },\n    \"tag\":   { \"kind\": \"string\", \"settings\": { \"enum\": [\"h1\",\"h2\",\"h3\",\"h4\",\"h5\",\"h6\",\"p\",\"div\",\"span\"] } },\n    \"link\":  { \"kind\": \"object\", \"shape\": { \"url\": { \"kind\": \"string\" }, \"is_external\": { \"kind\": \"boolean\" } } }\n  },\n  \"description\": \"Heading widget\",\n  \"llm_guidance\": {\n    \"can_have_children\": false,\n    \"default_styles\": { \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 2 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } } },\n    \"nesting\": { \"allowed_parents\": [\"e-flexbox\", \"e-div-block\"] }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor a container like `e-tabs`:\n\n```json\n\"llm_guidance\": {\n  \"can_have_children\": true,\n  \"nesting\": { \"allowed_child_types\": [\"e-tab\"] },\n  \"required_direct_children\": [\"e-tab\"]\n}\n```\n\n### `elementor://styles/schema/{category}`\n\nStyle properties are grouped into categories (`size`, `color`, `spacing`, `border`, `background`, `typography`, `layout`). Fetch the category that owns the property you're about to set.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"font-size\": {\n    \"kind\": \"union\",\n    \"prop_types\": {\n      \"size\":     { \"kind\": \"object\", \"shape\": { \"size\": { \"kind\": \"number\" }, \"unit\": { \"kind\": \"string\" } } },\n      \"variable\": { \"kind\": \"object\", \"settings\": { \"variable_type\": \"global-size-variable\" } }\n    }\n  },\n  \"color\": {\n    \"kind\": \"union\",\n    \"prop_types\": {\n      \"color\":    { \"kind\": \"object\", \"shape\": { \"$$type\": \"string\" } },\n      \"variable\": { \"kind\": \"object\", \"settings\": { \"variable_type\": \"global-color-variable\" } }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nUnion prop types are why `$$type` matters: `font-size` can be a literal `size` *or* a `global-size-variable` reference, and `$$type` selects which.\n\n### `elementor://global-variables`\n\nMap of variable id → variable record. Map by `label` yourself.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"var_a1b2\": { \"id\": \"var_a1b2\", \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-primary\",   \"value\": \"#0F766E\", \"version\": \"v4\" },\n  \"var_c3d4\": { \"id\": \"var_c3d4\", \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-accent\",    \"value\": \"#F59E0B\", \"version\": \"v4\" },\n  \"var_e5f6\": { \"id\": \"var_e5f6\", \"type\": \"global-font-variable\",  \"label\": \"font-display\",    \"value\": \"Playfair Display\", \"version\": \"v4\" },\n  \"var_g7h8\": { \"id\": \"var_g7h8\", \"type\": \"global-size-variable\",  \"label\": \"space-section\",   \"value\": \"6rem\",   \"version\": \"v4\" }\n}\n```\n\nVariable types (Pro-gated where noted):\n\n- `global-color-variable` — any CSS color\n- `global-font-variable` — font family name only (never a size)\n- `global-size-variable` *(Pro)* — simple length + unit (`16px`, `1.5rem`)\n- `global-custom-size-variable` *(Pro)* — any other CSS size expression (`clamp(...)`, `calc(...)`, `auto`, `300ms`)\n\nReferencing a variable in a style PropValue:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"color\": {\n    \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\",\n    \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_a1b2\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `elementor://global-classes`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"gc_xyz1\": {\n    \"id\": \"gc_xyz1\",\n    \"label\": \"heading-primary\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      { \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"font-size\":   { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 3.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n          \"font-weight\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"800\" },\n          \"color\":       { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_a1b2\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nA class is reused by adding its id to an element's `classes` setting (a `classes` PropValue — see the widget's schema for the exact shape).\n\n### `elementor://breakpoints/list`\n\nOnly enabled breakpoints. The full possible set is `widescreen`, `desktop`, `laptop`, `tablet_extra`, `tablet`, `mobile_extra`, `mobile` — but only ids in the response are valid in your output.\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"label\": \"Desktop\", \"constraint\": \"min\", \"value\": 1025 },\n  { \"label\": \"Tablet\",  \"constraint\": \"max\", \"value\": 1024 },\n  { \"label\": \"Mobile\",  \"constraint\": \"max\", \"value\": 767 }\n]\n```\n\n### `elementor://interactions/schema`\n\nDiscriminated union of legal interaction shapes for this site, reflecting Free vs Pro.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"triggers\": [\"load\", \"scrollIn\"],\n  \"effects\":  [\"fade\", \"slide\", \"scale\"],\n  \"easings\":  [\"easeIn\"],\n  \"pro\": {\n    \"active\": false,\n    \"extra_triggers\": [\"hover\", \"click\", \"scrollOn\", \"scrollOut\"],\n    \"extra_effects\":  [\"custom\"],\n    \"extra_easings\":  [\"easeInOut\", \"easeOut\", \"backIn\", \"backInOut\", \"backOut\", \"linear\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `elementor://context/general`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"timezone\": \"Asia/Jerusalem\",\n  \"postId\": 142,\n  \"currentPage\": { \"pageName\": \"Home\", \"pageTitle\": \"Home\", \"pageUrl\": \"/?post=142\" },\n  \"plugins\": { \"elementor-pro\": { \"active\": true, \"version\": \"3.x.y\" } }\n}\n```\n\nUse this for the current `version`/`postId` and to gate Pro-only emissions.\n\n## Wiring a discovery source\n\nFuture discovery sources should satisfy the data shapes above without changing `SKILL.md`. Add one of:\n\n1. MCP resources matching the `elementor://...` URIs.\n2. JSON dumps under `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/discovery/` using topic names like `global-variables.json`, `global-classes.json`, `breakpoints-list.json`, and `widgets-available.json`.\n3. A wp-env probe invoked by `validator/` or `import.sh` that writes the same shapes.\n\nThe one-shot flow should only need a source adapter that normalizes the source into the `DISCOVERY` block and leaves all design-system synthesis unchanged.\n\n## Template-import envelope\n\nThe file the user imports — Elementor → Templates → Import — has this exact root shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\":       \"0.4\",\n  \"title\":         \"Landing — Acme Pricing\",\n  \"type\":          \"page\",\n  \"page_settings\": { /* page-level settings, may be {} */ },\n  \"content\":       [ /* array of root V4 element nodes */ ]\n}\n```\n\nField notes:\n\n- `version` — the current Elementor DB version string. If the site exposes one through `elementor://context/general` use that; otherwise emit the latest version the editor accepts (`\"0.4\"` at time of writing).\n- `title` — used as the imported template's display name. Keep it human and specific (`\"Landing — Acme Pricing\"`, not `\"Untitled\"`).\n- `type` — `\"page\"` for a full page, `\"section\"` for a single drop-in section, `\"container\"` for a single container subtree. Match the user's intent.\n- `page_settings` — page-level overrides (background, custom CSS, padding). `{}` is fine when the user didn't specify any.\n- `content` — array of root nodes. For `type: \"page\"` this is typically a single root `e-flexbox` containing section flexboxes. For `type: \"section\"` or `type: \"container\"`, it's the one subtree the user will insert.\n\nThe same shape is what Elementor produces on export, so a round-trip works: export an existing page, study the JSON, mirror the shape.\n\n## Companion primitives (classes & variables)\n\nImported templates are self-contained: they reference global classes and variables by id, but **they do not create them**. If your tree references a class id or variable id, that primitive must already exist on the target site at import time.\n\nThere are two acceptable patterns:\n\n1. **Reuse only.** Restrict yourself to the class ids and variable ids already returned by `elementor://global-classes` and `elementor://global-variables`. The template imports cleanly with no preparation. Best for \"design within the existing system\".\n2. **Companion payload.** Alongside the template JSON, emit a small companion JSON that lists primitives to create before import. The user (or a wrapper script) creates them first, captures the assigned ids, substitutes those ids into the template, then imports.\n\n### Class catalog template\n\nThis is the baseline catalog for a polished landing page. Reuse a class when `elementor://global-classes` returns a matching id/label/variant; otherwise include the class in the companion payload below and reference it with `@@label:<class-label>` placeholders until ids are assigned. Variable placeholders use the same convention.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"section-wrap\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=section-wrap\",\n    \"label\": \"section-wrap\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n          \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n          \"align-items\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"center\" },\n          \"padding\": { \"$$type\": \"dimensions\", \"value\": { \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 6, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 6, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"mobile\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"padding\": { \"$$type\": \"dimensions\", \"value\": { \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 3.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 3.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"content-wrap\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=content-wrap\",\n    \"label\": \"content-wrap\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n          \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n          \"gap\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 100, \"unit\": \"%\" } },\n          \"max-width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 72, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"heading-display\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=heading-display\",\n    \"label\": \"heading-display\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 4.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"font-weight\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"800\" },\n          \"line-height\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 0.95 },\n          \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-ink\" } }\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"mobile\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2.75, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"heading-section\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=heading-section\",\n    \"label\": \"heading-section\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"font-weight\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"750\" },\n          \"line-height\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.1 },\n          \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-ink\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"body-text\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=body-text\",\n    \"label\": \"body-text\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.125, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"line-height\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.7 },\n          \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-muted\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"cta-primary\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=cta-primary\",\n    \"label\": \"cta-primary\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#5B3DF5\" } } },\n          \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" },\n          \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 999, \"unit\": \"px\" } },\n          \"padding\": { \"$$type\": \"dimensions\", \"value\": { \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 0.875, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 0.875, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"cta-ghost\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=cta-ghost\",\n    \"label\": \"cta-ghost\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" } } },\n          \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-primary\" } },\n          \"border-width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"px\" } },\n          \"border-style\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"solid\" },\n          \"border-color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-primary\" } },\n          \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 999, \"unit\": \"px\" } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"card-surface\": {\n    \"match\": \"elementor://global-classes label=card-surface\",\n    \"label\": \"card-surface\",\n    \"variants\": [\n      {\n        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n        \"custom_css\": null,\n        \"props\": {\n          \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n          \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n          \"gap\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" } } },\n          \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.25, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n          \"padding\": { \"$$type\": \"dimensions\", \"value\": { \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe companion payload shape below is the wire format for every `create` entry from this catalog.\n\n### Companion payload shape\n\nCompanion payload shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"variables\": [\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-primary\", \"value\": \"#0F766E\" },\n    { \"type\": \"global-font-variable\",  \"label\": \"font-display\",  \"value\": \"Playfair Display\" }\n  ],\n  \"classes\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"button-cta\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        { \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null }, \"props\": { /* PropValues — may reference variables by placeholder label */ } }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nWhen the companion approach is used, the template body may reference variables/classes by **placeholder label** rather than by real id; the wrapper script that consumes both files substitutes labels for the ids returned when the primitives are created. Use `{ \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-primary\" }` as the placeholder convention so substitution is unambiguous (do NOT use the nested `{\"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": ...}` format as it will fail Elementor V4 global classes schema validation). The wrapper replaces every `@@label:<name>` with the real id before import.\n\n#### Critical Style Schema Rules for Companion & Local Styles:\n- **Global Variable References**: Must be a plain string ID, e.g., `{\"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-primary\"}` or `{\"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": \"e-gv-brand-primary\"}`. Any nesting like `{\"value\": {\"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": ...}}` is schema-invalid and causes import failure.\n- **Line Height (`line-height`)**: Must always be a `size` PropType in V4, e.g., `{\"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": {\"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"em\"}}`. It is **never** a `number` or `string` PropType. Using `{\"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5}` will cause the parser to fail and discard the entire global class snapshot.\n\nIf you can't tell which pattern the user wants, default to **reuse only** and tell them what's available; create new primitives only when nothing on the site fits.\n";

export const examplesDocs = "# Examples — V4 page generation\n\nComposite discovery-first example, then three trees demonstrating lower-level mechanics. Then a global-class definition and a complete importable template file.\n\n> **Key rule repeated here:** flex layout (`flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap`) always goes in `styles[id].variants[0].props`, never only in `settings`. Widget text content uses `html-v3` (see widget content key table in `SKILL.md`).\n\n## Example 0 — Discovery → catalog → classes-first tree + companion payload\n\nBrief: generate a pricing section for a SaaS landing page. Both variants emit the same tree shape; the difference is whether discovery can reuse existing primitives or must create companion primitives.\n\n### Variant A — current workspace, no discovery source\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { all: default }\n  pro_active: false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, e-paragraph, e-button, e-image, e-tabs, e-tab, e-svg, e-divider, e-youtube]\n  variables:\n    reuse: []\n    create:\n      - { label: brand-primary, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#5B3DF5\" }\n      - { label: brand-ink, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#171321\" }\n      - { label: brand-muted, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#6F6A7C\" }\n      - { label: space-section, type: global-size-variable, value: \"6rem\" }\n  classes:\n    reuse: []\n    create:\n      - { label: section-wrap, source: section-wrap }\n      - { label: content-wrap, source: content-wrap }\n      - { label: heading-section, source: heading-section }\n      - { label: body-text, source: body-text }\n      - { label: card-surface, source: card-surface }\n      - { label: cta-primary, source: cta-primary }\n  design_guidelines_source: .cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md\n  discovery_gaps: [context/general, global-variables, global-classes, widgets/available, breakpoints/list]\n\nDESIGN_SYSTEM:\n  catalog:\n    section-wrap:    { kind: create, ref: section-wrap, props_summary: \"centered vertical section using @@label:space-section\" }\n    content-wrap:    { kind: create, ref: content-wrap, props_summary: \"max-width column with shared gap\" }\n    heading-section: { kind: create, ref: heading-section, props_summary: \"section h2 using @@label:brand-ink\" }\n    body-text:       { kind: create, ref: body-text, props_summary: \"muted paragraph text\" }\n    card-surface:    { kind: create, ref: card-surface, props_summary: \"white rounded pricing card\" }\n    cta-primary:     { kind: create, ref: cta-primary, props_summary: \"filled brand button\" }\n  tree_class_usage_target: \">= 60% containers and >= 50% widgets reference catalog classes\"\n```\n\n`pricing-section.json`:\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"el_pricing_section\",\n    \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Section\" },\n    \"settings\": {\n      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:section-wrap\"] }\n    },\n    \"elements\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"el_pricing_content\",\n        \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n        \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Content\" },\n        \"settings\": {\n          \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:content-wrap\", \"local_pricing_content_gap\"] }\n        },\n        \"styles\": {\n          \"local_pricing_content_gap\": {\n            \"id\": \"local_pricing_content_gap\",\n            \"label\": \"local\",\n            \"type\": \"class\",\n            \"variants\": [\n              {\n                \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                \"custom_css\": null,\n                \"props\": {\n                  \"gap\": {\n                    \"$$type\": \"global-size-variable\",\n                    \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:space-section\" }\n                  }\n                }\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"elements\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_heading\",\n            \"elType\": \"widget\",\n            \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Heading\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:heading-section\"] },\n              \"title\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h2>Plans that scale with you</h2>\" }, \"children\": [] } },\n              \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h2\" }\n            }\n          },\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_intro\",\n            \"elType\": \"widget\",\n            \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Intro\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:body-text\"] },\n              \"paragraph\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start small, then add seats and workflows when your team grows.</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } }\n            }\n          },\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_cards\",\n            \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Cards\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:content-wrap\"] }\n            },\n            \"elements\": [\n              {\n                \"id\": \"el_pricing_card_growth\",\n                \"elType\": \"e-div-block\",\n                \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Plan\" },\n                \"settings\": {\n                  \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:card-surface\"] }\n                },\n                \"elements\": [\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_title\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Title\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:heading-section\"] },\n                      \"title\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h3>Growth</h3>\" }, \"children\": [] } },\n                      \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h3\" }\n                    }\n                  },\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_copy\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Copy\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:body-text\"] },\n                      \"paragraph\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>For teams building repeatable launch motions.</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } }\n                    }\n                  },\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_cta\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-button\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth CTA\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"@@label:cta-primary\"] },\n                      \"text\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start Growth</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } }\n                    }\n                  }\n                ]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\n`pricing-section.companion.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"variables\": [\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-primary\", \"value\": \"#5B3DF5\" },\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-ink\", \"value\": \"#171321\" },\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-muted\", \"value\": \"#6F6A7C\" },\n    { \"type\": \"global-size-variable\", \"label\": \"space-section\", \"value\": \"6rem\" }\n  ],\n  \"classes\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"section-wrap\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n            \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n            \"align-items\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"center\" },\n            \"padding\": { \"$$type\": \"dimensions\", \"value\": { \"block-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 6, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"block-end\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 6, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }, \"inline-start\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"content-wrap\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n            \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n            \"gap\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n            \"width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 100, \"unit\": \"%\" } },\n            \"max-width\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 72, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"heading-section\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n            \"font-weight\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"750\" },\n            \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-ink\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"body-text\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.125, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n            \"line-height\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.7 },\n            \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-muted\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"card-surface\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" },\n            \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n            \"gap\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1, \"unit\": \"rem\" } },\n            \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" } } },\n            \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 1.25, \"unit\": \"rem\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"cta-primary\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#5B3DF5\" } } },\n            \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#ffffff\" },\n            \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 999, \"unit\": \"px\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Variant B — future workspace, MCP or dump available\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { context: mcp, variables: mcp, classes: mcp, widgets: mcp, breakpoints: mcp }\n  pro_active: true\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, e-paragraph, e-button, e-image]\n  variables:\n    reuse:\n      - { id: var_primary_01, label: brand-primary, type: global-color-variable }\n      - { id: var_space_section, label: space-section, type: global-size-variable }\n    create:\n      - { label: brand-ink, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#171321\" }\n      - { label: brand-muted, type: global-color-variable, value: \"#6F6A7C\" }\n  classes:\n    reuse:\n      - { id: gc_section_wrap, label: section-wrap }\n      - { id: gc_card_surface, label: card-surface }\n    create:\n      - { label: content-wrap, source: content-wrap }\n      - { label: heading-section, source: heading-section }\n      - { label: body-text, source: body-text }\n      - { label: cta-primary, source: cta-primary }\n  design_guidelines_source: .cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md\n  discovery_gaps: []\n\nDESIGN_SYSTEM:\n  catalog:\n    section-wrap:    { kind: reuse, ref: gc_section_wrap, props_summary: \"existing section wrapper\" }\n    content-wrap:    { kind: create, ref: content-wrap, props_summary: \"max-width column with shared gap\" }\n    heading-section: { kind: create, ref: heading-section, props_summary: \"section h2 using @@label:brand-ink\" }\n    body-text:       { kind: create, ref: body-text, props_summary: \"muted paragraph text\" }\n    card-surface:    { kind: reuse, ref: gc_card_surface, props_summary: \"existing rounded card surface\" }\n    cta-primary:     { kind: create, ref: cta-primary, props_summary: \"filled brand button using var_primary_01\" }\n```\n\nIn this variant, the tree is identical except reused classes/variables use real ids:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_pricing_section\",\n  \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Section\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"gc_section_wrap\", \"local_pricing_content_gap\"] }\n      },\n      \"styles\": {\n        \"local_pricing_content_gap\": {\n          \"id\": \"local_pricing_content_gap\",\n          \"label\": \"local\",\n          \"type\": \"class\",\n          \"variants\": [\n            {\n              \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n              \"custom_css\": null,\n              \"props\": {\n                \"gap\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"global-size-variable\",\n                  \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_space_section\" }\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n  },\n  \"elements\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_pricing_card_growth\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-div-block\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Plan\" },\n      \"settings\": {\n        \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"gc_card_surface\"] }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n`pricing-section.companion.json` shrinks because `section-wrap`, `card-surface`, `brand-primary`, and `space-section` were reused:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"variables\": [\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-ink\", \"value\": \"#171321\" },\n    { \"type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"label\": \"brand-muted\", \"value\": \"#6F6A7C\" }\n  ],\n  \"classes\": [\n    { \"label\": \"content-wrap\", \"variants\": [{ \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null }, \"custom_css\": null, \"props\": { \"display\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"flex\" }, \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" } } }] },\n    { \"label\": \"heading-section\", \"variants\": [{ \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null }, \"custom_css\": null, \"props\": { \"font-size\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": 2.5, \"unit\": \"rem\" } } } }] },\n    { \"label\": \"body-text\", \"variants\": [{ \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null }, \"custom_css\": null, \"props\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"@@label:brand-muted\" } } } }] },\n    { \"label\": \"cta-primary\", \"variants\": [{ \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null }, \"custom_css\": null, \"props\": { \"background\": { \"$$type\": \"background\", \"value\": { \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": \"#5B3DF5\" } } } } }] }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nExamples 1-3 below show the lower-level mechanics used by this composite example: node nesting, class/local variant layering, variables, and interactions.\n\n## Example 1 — Nested container with `required_direct_children`\n\nDemonstrates: containers nest other containers; `e-tabs` requires direct `e-tab` children; non-container widgets (`e-heading`, `e-paragraph`) sit at the leaves. Flex layout on the outer container is in `styles`, not `settings`.\n\n> **Container `elType` rule (v4):** Container elements (`e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-tabs`, `e-tab`, etc.) use their own name as `elType` and have **no `widgetType` field**. Leaf widgets (`e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, …) use `elType: \"widget\"` + `widgetType`. This matches the SKILL.md `elType`/`widgetType` table and is the pattern used in all repo output files.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_feature_section\",\n  \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Feature Tabs\" },\n  \"settings\": {},\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"local_feature_section_1\": {\n      \"id\": \"local_feature_section_1\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"props\": {\n            \"flex-direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n            \"gap\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"size\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 3 },\n                \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"elements\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_section_heading\",\n      \"elType\": \"widget\",\n      \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Section Heading\" },\n      \"settings\": {\n        \"title\": {\n          \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n          \"value\": {\n            \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h2>What's inside</h2>\" },\n            \"children\": []\n          }\n        },\n        \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h2\" }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_tabs\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-tabs\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Feature Tabs\" },\n      \"settings\": {},\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_tab_1\",\n          \"elType\": \"e-tab\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tab — Performance\" },\n          \"settings\": { \"label\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Performance</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } } },\n          \"elements\": [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"el_tab_1_body\",\n              \"elType\": \"widget\",\n              \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n              \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Performance copy\" },\n              \"settings\": { \"paragraph\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Sub-50ms TTFB on cold cache.</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } } }\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_tab_2\",\n          \"elType\": \"e-tab\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tab — Security\" },\n          \"settings\": { \"label\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Security</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } } },\n          \"elements\": [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"el_tab_2_body\",\n              \"elType\": \"widget\",\n              \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n              \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Security copy\" },\n              \"settings\": { \"paragraph\": { \"$$type\": \"html-v3\", \"value\": { \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>SOC 2 Type II, audited yearly.</p>\" }, \"children\": [] } } }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nEmitting `e-tabs` with zero `e-tab` children is rejected at import. Even if the user asks for \"a tabs widget\", supply tabs.\n\n## Example 2 — Global class + local override at a specific breakpoint + hover state\n\nDemonstrates the three-layer styling model on one element: it consumes the reusable `card-elevated` global class, adds a local one-off padding tweak that only applies on mobile, and a local hover state. Variants prove that breakpoint and state are the same mechanism.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_pricing_card\",\n  \"elType\": \"e-div-block\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Card — Pro\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"classes\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"classes\",\n      \"value\": [\"gc_card_elevated_id\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"local_pricing_card_1\": {\n      \"id\": \"local_pricing_card_1\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"mobile\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"padding\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"spacing\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"top\":    { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                \"right\":  { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                \"bottom\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                \"left\":   { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": \"hover\" },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"transform\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"translateY(-4px)\" },\n            \"box-shadow\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"0 30px 60px rgba(15,118,110,0.18)\" }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nTwo things: (1) the class is referenced by id (`gc_card_elevated_id`), not by label; you fetched `elementor://global-classes` to get that id. (2) Hover and the mobile padding override are *two variants of the same local style definition* — not two separate definitions.\n\n## Example 3 — Variable-referenced color + per-element interaction\n\nDemonstrates: variables resolve via id wrapped in a `global-color-variable` PropValue; interactions attach to the element directly. Note `e-button` uses content key `text` with `$$type: html-v3`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_primary_cta\",\n  \"elType\": \"widget\",\n  \"widgetType\": \"e-button\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Primary CTA\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"text\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start free trial</p>\" },\n        \"children\": []\n      }\n    },\n    \"link\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"link\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"destination\":   { \"$$type\": \"url\",     \"value\": \"/signup\" },\n        \"isTargetBlank\": { \"$$type\": \"boolean\", \"value\": false }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"local_cta_1\": {\n      \"id\": \"local_cta_1\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"custom_css\": null,\n          \"props\": {\n            \"background-color\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\",\n              \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_a1b2\" }\n            },\n            \"color\": { \"$$type\": \"color\", \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"#FFFFFF\" } }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"interactions\": {\n    \"version\": 1,\n    \"items\": [\n      {\n        \"value\": {\n          \"interaction_id\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"tmp_int_cta_1\" },\n          \"trigger\":        { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"scrollIn\" },\n          \"animation\": {\n            \"$$type\": \"object\",\n            \"value\": {\n              \"effect\":    { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"fade\" },\n              \"type\":      { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"in\" },\n              \"direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"bottom\" },\n              \"timing_config\": {\n                \"$$type\": \"object\",\n                \"value\": {\n                  \"duration\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 600 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"ms\" } } },\n                  \"delay\":    { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 100 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"ms\" } } }\n                }\n              },\n              \"config\": {\n                \"$$type\": \"object\",\n                \"value\": { \"easing\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"easeIn\" } }\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          \"breakpoints\": { \"$$type\": \"array\", \"value\": [] }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`var_a1b2` is the id you got from the global-variables resource for label `brand-primary` — never the label itself in the payload. `easeIn` is the only free-tier easing.\n\n## Global-class definition\n\nTwo variants on one class: a `default` baseline and a `hover` state that references a different variable. Goes into the companion-primitives payload, not into the template body.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"button-cta\",\n  \"variants\": [\n    {\n      \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n      \"custom_css\": null,\n      \"props\": {\n        \"padding\": {\n          \"$$type\": \"spacing\",\n          \"value\": {\n            \"top\":    { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1 },   \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n            \"right\":  { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 2.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n            \"bottom\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1 },   \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n            \"left\":   { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 2.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } }\n          }\n        },\n        \"border-radius\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 0.5 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n        \"background-color\": {\n          \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\",\n          \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_a1b2\" }\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": \"hover\" },\n      \"custom_css\": null,\n      \"props\": {\n        \"background-color\": {\n          \"$$type\": \"global-color-variable\",\n          \"value\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"var_c3d4\" }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Complete importable template file\n\nA minimal but complete `type: \"section\"` template the user can import directly. Drop it into a `.json` file and use Elementor → Templates → Import.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"0.4\",\n  \"title\":   \"CTA Section — Trial Signup\",\n  \"type\":    \"section\",\n  \"page_settings\": {},\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_cta_root\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Section\" },\n      \"settings\": {},\n      \"styles\": {\n        \"local_cta_root_1\": {\n          \"id\": \"local_cta_root_1\",\n          \"label\": \"local\",\n          \"type\": \"class\",\n          \"variants\": [\n            {\n              \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n              \"custom_css\": null,\n              \"props\": {\n                \"flex-direction\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"column\" },\n                \"align-items\":     { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"center\" },\n                \"justify-content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"center\" },\n                \"gap\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"size\",\n                  \"value\": {\n                    \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 1.5 },\n                    \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" }\n                  }\n                },\n                \"padding\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"spacing\",\n                  \"value\": {\n                    \"top\":    { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 8 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                    \"right\":  { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 2 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                    \"bottom\": { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 8 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } },\n                    \"left\":   { \"$$type\": \"size\", \"value\": { \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"number\", \"value\": 2 }, \"unit\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rem\" } } }\n                  }\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      },\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_heading\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Heading\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"title\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h2>Ready when you are.</h2>\" },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            },\n            \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h2\" }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_sub\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Subhead\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"paragraph\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Spin up a project in under 60 seconds. No credit card.</p>\" },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_button\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-button\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Primary CTA\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"text\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start free trial</p>\" },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            },\n            \"link\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"link\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"destination\":   { \"$$type\": \"url\",     \"value\": \"/signup\" },\n                \"isTargetBlank\": { \"$$type\": \"boolean\", \"value\": false }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis template references no global classes or variables, so it imports cleanly against any site. To use variables/classes, follow the companion-primitives flow in `reference.md`.\n";

export const designGuidelinesDocs = "# Design guidelines — Elementor V4 JSON generation\n\nPrescriptive rules for **authoring** template JSON (global variables, global classes, `styles` props, copy, structure). Validators use `validate-elementor-page/visual-rubric.md` for screenshot scoring; keep generation guidance here so skills stay separated.\n\n## Philosophy\n\nBuild **distinctive, high-fidelity** layouts — not anonymous wireframes. Every page should read as a deliberate product: intentional color, typography hierarchy, and section rhythm. Aim for polished UI, not default browser chrome.\n\n### User specification is law\n\nWhen the brief names **hex colors**, **fonts**, **section order**, **copy**, **locale/RTL**, or references a **screenshot/URL**, those choices override convenience defaults. Encode them in variables, classes, and widget content exactly. Output that ignores an explicit user constraint is wrong.\n\nWhen the user gives **no** visual spec, you still owe a cohesive system: derive a small palette, type scale, and spacing rhythm from `PAGE_TYPE`, `BRAND_COLORS` (if any), and `SECTIONS`.\n\n---\n\n## Bold direction (commit before you branch the tree)\n\nAnswer briefly (internally or in notes to yourself):\n\n1. **Purpose & audience** — Who lands here and what should they do?\n2. **Tone** — Pick and hold one direction (e.g. editorial, brutalist/minimal, soft retail, luxury restraint, playful, utilitarian). Intensity is optional; **intentionality** is not.\n3. **Differentiation** — What one thing should this page be remembered for? (Asymmetry, typographic drama, a single strong accent, unusual section order, etc.)\n\nThen execute that direction in **JSON only**: variables, class props, flex layout, imagery choices, and real copy — not generic placeholders.\n\n---\n\n## Typography (Elementor-native)\n\n- Encode **`font-family`** (and weight/size/line-height) in **global classes** or local `styles[…].variants[…].props` using valid PropValue shapes from the style schema.\n- Prefer **two roles**: a display / heading treatment and a body treatment. Use **large weight contrast** between hero headline and body (e.g. 700 vs 400; size ratio 3×+ when the brief allows).\n- **Avoid defaulting every project** to the same “safe” pairing (e.g. Inter + Inter) when the brief is open — pick stacks that match the tone: distinctive webfonts, or a deliberate **system UI** stack (`system-ui`, `-apple-system`, `Segoe UI`, sans-serif) for crisp product UI.\n- **Line-height** must stay proportional to font-size (see `SKILL.md` pre-handoff checklist). Never use absolute line-heights smaller than the font size on headings.\n\n---\n\n## Color & theme\n\n- Prefer **one dominant** brand/adjacent color, **one accent**, and **tinted neutrals** — not five accents at equal weight.\n- Express colors as **`global-color-variable`** entries in the companion payload when they repeat; reference by id in props.\n- **Purple–blue gradients on white** are a known generic pattern — use only when the brief or brand demands purple.\n- Tint neutrals toward warm or cool to match the palette; flat `#f5f5f5` / `#333` with zero temperature reads as unfinished.\n\n---\n\n## Motion\n\n- Use **`interactions`** sparingly (see `SKILL.md`): 2–3 high-impact moments (hero reveal, primary CTA, one featured block). Respect Pro vs free triggers.\n- Prefer **one orchestrated** load/stagger story over scattered micro-motion on every widget.\n\n---\n\n## Spatial composition\n\n- Prefer **asymmetry**, mixed column ratios, overlap, or broken grids over “hero centered + three equal cards” when the playbook allows.\n- Vary **section vertical rhythm** — not identical `padding-block` on every section unless the brief is a strict system.\n- Respect **`layout-in-styles`**: flex lives in `styles[…].props`, not only in `settings`.\n\n---\n\n## Backgrounds & depth\n\n- Alternate section surfaces (subtle tints, thin borders, restrained shadow) so the page is not one flat `#fff` field.\n- Use **`background`** PropValue (schema-shaped), gradients, or images where they support the tone — not decorative noise unrelated to content.\n- Cards and tiles: controlled **`border-radius`** and **box-shadow** from the catalog (`card-surface`, etc.) unless the brief demands sharp flat UI.\n\n---\n\n## Copy & content\n\n- **No vague hype** (“Revolutionize your workflow”) unless the brief uses that voice. Prefer concrete outcomes, numbers, and product truth.\n- **No Elementor default strings** in shipped trees (`This is a title`, `Type your paragraph here`, `Click here`).\n\n---\n\n## JSON-level anti-slop (clichés to avoid in structure and tokens)\n\nWhen the brief does not explicitly require these patterns, avoid:\n\n- **Three-up feature grid** as the only layout idea (icon → title → blurb ×3, repeated identically).\n- **Perfect symmetry everywhere** (image left / text right / repeat forever).\n- **Identical card heights and radii** on every surface — vary featured vs compact where it helps hierarchy.\n- **Emoji as icons** — use `e-image` / SVG or `e-icon` when available per discovery.\n- **Trusted-by logo bar** immediately under the hero without brief support.\n- **Magic dust** decor (random floating shapes) with no brand or content rationale.\n- **Rounded corners identical on every control** — mix radii intentionally (pills vs sharp vs one soft family).\n\nThese are **authoring** rules. The validator’s **`visual-rubric.md`** adds screenshot-specific failure lines (e.g. visible “AI template” tells).\n\n---\n\n## Consistency with `validate-elementor-page`\n\nGenerators should satisfy both this file and the visual rubric. If you choose **system UI** stacks, set them **explicitly** in styles so the front does not fall back to browser default serif. If you choose **webfonts**, set `font-family` to real stack strings the engine can resolve (Google/font CDN is a site concern — still emit the intended `font-family` names in JSON).\n\n---\n\n## Resolution\n\nAgents read this file for discovery topic `design_guidelines` in this order:\n\n1. `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md` (this file)\n2. `<workspace-root>/design-guidelines.md` if (1) is missing\n\nIf neither exists, use inline brief + `SKILL.md` / `reference.md` defaults.\n";
